This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel framework for uncertainty estimation in deep learning. It also mentions that the proposed framework is agnostic to the network architecture and task, which is a common characteristic of machine learning research. 

The paper also deals with computer vision and control tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.RO (Robotics). 

Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Bayesian belief networks and Monte-Carlo sampling, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, the paper deals with neural networks, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
